<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100547716367404></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100547716367404><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100547716367404>a delf mag</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100547716367404#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=118149><span id= >pietwigus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 11th 6:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok evryone talks about how a gnome is the best race for a mag. Why not make it fun a play somethin evil MWAHAHA!!!! Withi the Kunark expansion it is soo easy to make lvl 1-41 on an evil mag in less than 16 days played time. I did it and this was my first char. wanna know how I did it? Well here's what I did. <br>  First of all from lvl 1-6 stay in nec forest killin everything but the guards once you reach about lvl 6 I recommend findin either a halfing group/undead ruin group/ or head to EC for orc an Orc camp group.<br>  after bout lvl 11-12 try and find a Derv group in WC or Nro just make sure you stay away from the one with the delf in it you'll lose faction with the indigo brotherhood if you kill him and that means being KOS to Home not a good thing at this lvl. also around 10 you start soloin most of the mob's in EC. <br>  At lvl 12-16 I rotated between Orc Highway groups in Oasis and soling in the entrance to Lava storm mountains. GREAT xp and few people around to steal mobs away. Just watch out for the Fire imps and Lava basilisks they kinda Under con'd. I used the pull to pet method and stuck to water pet it works awesome on them fiery mobs lol<br>  After 16 it was off to Kunark. Hop on that fine Barrel barge in Oasis and onto the Boat on Oowomps Isle in Timorous Deep and head to Overthere. Now once in Over there you have 2 options. You can either invis and head to the ledge, get a sow and lev from a nice druid, and head to "Lake of ill omen" through Frontier Mountains, or just set up camp on the Ne side of the Outpost right by that nice golem who you can run to for any needed help if ya get too many aggro's. The mobs on the NE corner range around lvl 14-somewhere in the high teens. You can easily solo there to lvl 20. Make sure to stay on the NE corner of the zone because the mob's quickly jump to 30+ as you head south and west away from the outpost. <br>    Ok at lvl 20 I headed over to LOIO and got into Sarnak fort Groups and Goblin groups. also soloin around 4 pillars will keeps you from getting bored while your LFG. Make sure you can everything a mob could be blue one time and the next be yellow or above.<br>    After 25-26 I recommend finding an Mountain Giant fort group in FM, and make sure you have a couple of Dimensional pockets in your inven for some of the cool drops like "Giant Tree Flayer" etc. Just make sure you take a trip to the outpost before you log so you can sell the items in the dim pockets or else they and everything in them will vanish when you log off.<br>   Ok once you make lvl 29 for the best xp I recommend headin back to Overthere and grabbin a ledge group Awesome xp all the way to lvl 39 Horrible loot though. <br>   Now also in your mid 30's it would be a good idea to grab a group to go down to Cazick Thule and huntin them gators for your Focus Item drops ie Shovel,broom,torche, and stein. Also Those words of mastery for your epic drop there. <br>   After Cazick thule it might be a good Idea to drag your group to Rather mountains and kill a few of them Mountain Giants and Cyclops since your close &lt;smiles&gt;. You need both of those mobs toes for focus items also. <br>   Now Once you reach lvl 39 it's off to the Dread Lands and You'll be there until your 50's atleast that's what I've discovered I still only lvl 41 at this moment. Well that's my guide to you delfs who decided on the awesome race of a mag. Oh one more thing "USE YOUR HOTKEYS" Chanties love a mag who can control his pet through the use of hot keys.<br><br>Here's a list of how my hotkeys are laid out.<br><br>#2 dd<br>/sit off<br>/assist (who ever the main tank is)<br>/puase 5 (allows for target to change over before you begin to cast)<br>/cast 1 (or whatever #gem your dd is on<br>/pause ## (casting time of spell), One order fried %T comming up<br><br><br>#3 pet attack<br>/sit off<br>/assist (main tanks name)<br>/pause 5<br>/pet attack<br>/g %M assisting on %T<br><br>#4 Pet Back<br>/sit off<br>/pet back off<br>/g %M is Backing off %T<br><br>Those are the main ones needed whe groupin with a chantie. Make sure you add the group say text that way the chantie know exactly what your pet and you are doing. Mag's have gotten a bad rap by chanties for breakin Mezz's. By players not know how to control they're pets. well that's all hope this will help any of you delfs looking to play a mag. BE EVIL IT MORE FUN MWAHAHAHA!!!!!!!! <br>&nbsp;<br>Pietwig lvl 41 (dark elf)<br>Magician</td></tr>
