	   <tr><td colspan=2>*poke poke*<br><br>     Umm... yeah, pure casters can mele. With a decent weapon they can actually do a decent job of it. Granted, yer not gonna wanna mele in a group much, but when you're wandering around and something green aggros ya, it's nice to not have to repeatedly hit the nuke button and pray that you don't get interrupted.<br>     It's a slim advantage, but it's one that's easy to get. There's really no reason to not pracice a few mele skills. In lower level battles where you're in a good group, or if you're soloing and get it running, just take a few wacks at it with a stick. Got my 1hb up to 100 that way, it's not great, but with a journeyman's staff or other decent weapon, you can actually do pretty decent damage. Also handy if you need to take a few licks to keep your pet from getting killed. Granted, yer not gonna be able to tank much, or long, but at lvl 30 it's a skill that's served me VERY well.<br>     Mobs will always go after you over your pet if you're in smacking range, if you're low on mana and your pet's low on life, just toss a few of those nifty AC and regen self buffs on, a DS, and get in there! Don't expect to tank like a warrior, but you can do decent damage, keep it off your pet while your pet attacks it, and MAYBE make it run before you have to high tail it to the zone.<br><br>It doesn't help loads, but it does help. And I know ya get the whole "what's the best" question a ton, but try not to get bitter about it. Newbies need to learn too.<br><br>Just my 2cp... of course there is the whole thing with me being out of my damn mind, but I'm mad, not ill. And trust me on this one folx, it does help.<br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, The Mad Mage of Povar<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
