	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Chain casting is a strategy for fighting relatively high level mobs, against which you will normally lose.  Send the pet to fight, and when it's at half health or so, start casting your pet again.  When you're casting, type in /pet get lost in the text bar but DON'T hit "Enter" yet.  Hit "Enter" when the spell is almost finished casting, so your current pet disappears and you summon a new one.  (You must make sure that your current pet never gets killed when you chain cast, because the mob will start attacking you and without a pet, the battle is lost).  Keep on chain-casting your pet until the mob is dead.<br><br>I have a few questions about this strategy myself.<br><br>1) What pet is the most effective?<br><br>2) Should I cast Burnout on the pet?<br><br>3) Should I cast a damage shield on the pet?<br><br>4) any other advice?<br><br>Thanks for the help :)<br><br>Rascarcapac, level 45 Magician, Xev server.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
