<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100516386160817></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100516386160817><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100516386160817>RE: Solo go for it</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100516386160817#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 7th 3:11 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think that the Air pet is better than the Earth pet as a tank, for a number of reasons:<br><br>1) In a brawl, the Air pet lasts longer.  Even though the Earth pet has more HP, the Air pet's high agility means that it gets hit a lot less.  In the end, the Air pet will last longer than the Earth pet.<br><br>2) The Air pet's stun spell keeps the mob from swinging while the Earth pet's root spell does not.<br><br>3) The Earth pet's root will keep heavily injured mobs in place, so that the mob fights to the death.  This results in the Earth pet taking additional damage.<br><br>Instead of as a main tank, I prefer to use the Earth pet for these situations:<br><br>- When you want to kill the mob quickly.  The earth pet keeps the mob in place so you can nuke recklessly without worrying about over-taunting the mob and having it attack you.<br><br>- When you are in a dungeon.  The earth pet prevents an injured mob from training other mobs onto you.<br><br>The Fire and Water pets also have their uses.<br><br>Fire: for fighting green mobs (often more than one at a time).  The fire pet has a great damage shield, much stronger than your own, that will make short work of mobs that hit it.  This is especially effective when more than one mob is hitting the pet.  However, you have to watch its hit points because it is the least tough of your four pets.<br><br>Water: for Pet kiting and for any situation where another pet won't fit.  With good HP and no real specialty, the Water pet is the balanced elemental that works for almost any situation.  (Pet kiting is overnuking the mob to have it chase you, and then to run around in circles while the pet hits the mob from behind.  Don't do this without either speeding up yourself or slowing down the mob.)<br><br>I don't think that there's one pet that is the best in every situation.  I found that I've used all four pets in different situations.  Hope this helps. :)<br><br>Rascarcapac, level 45 Magician, Xev server.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
