	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, I think some of you are confused...I maybe just read the first few posts, but a lot of you have this sick obsession with grouping.  If you're a mage, then you don't need a group...you have a group.  You summon up a pet, cast burnout, give it a summoned weapon and a fire shield, then let it tank while you nuke from a distance.  I'm only level 12 and the only times I group is with my close friend who has an enchanter (big bonus to have a mob feared while you're pet beats it and you and your friend nukes).  But for the most part, you're a soloist.  Remember this...even at higher levels mages can still solo...next to maybe druids they are the single best solo class in the game. <br><br>As for strategies, like I said, be greedy and don't share the experience with people.  I started off at the Nek newb log killing little stuff, then got PLed to 8 (hey, when a high level friend says he's gonna help me kill dervs at level 5, I don't argue with him).  Then I soloed Darkweed Snakes in EC until about 10 (this is a great strategy...you have a water pet that'll resist their poison.  Use it), which was great experience cause they were mostly yellow until 10ish.  Then I made my way to 12 with willowisps in EC and shrivled mummies, giant scarabs, madmen, and dune tarantulas in North Ro.  I'm currently soloing both alluring sirens out in OoT.  Anyways, just a suggestion.  My friend says that I should solo the sirens till about 18 or so, then go after the named aviaks until 24 or so...then he says get my RoE, and then when I eventually hit 30, go to the Great Divide out in Velious and kill Tizmacks...that's where he stopped giving advice.  He said that'll get me to about 35, 36...then he said something about a certain creature at Timorous Deep...but I'll find out about that when I hit 36.<br><br>Bottom line, if you're starting a mage (the smart thing to do if you want to level without having to beg for a group) expect a lot of solo activities, because like I said you have a built in tank.  Oh, and if you have a human mage, delete it and return your copy of EQ, because you suck and don't understand good race/class combinations....sorry, but I see a lot of those idiots in East Freeport and I just want to smack them for their stupidity....k, that's all from me.<br><br>Glete, dark elf mage (Rallos Zek...the only good server)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
