	   <tr><td colspan=2>I disagree. Rain spells are only a high taunt if you don't have a partner wacking away at the mob. In a group, you can cast a high damage rain, followed by a nuke and STILL probably not have to worry about catching aggro. To make em hit just debuff the mob first. works wonders.<br><br>Debuff rain also works well for soloing, The air pet's stun slowly resets the aggro, and with a debuff on em, it works quite fast.<br><br>Yer right on one thing though, don't bother with rain spells before 29, they only hit twice, if they hit. Even if both do, it's still less damage than a single DD.<br><br>The 29 spell tho is yummy. Three shots of 97 damage each. Even if one misses, you've still outdamaged your best nuke, with less aggro and only like 20 more mana per cast. And with a debuff on em first (which ya really outta be doing anyway) ya still got about a 4 outta 5 chance of it hitting.<br><br>That's saying nothing of overpulls. A good rain spell cast on an overpull can save a group's lives. Ya may catch aggro from one, but by that time you'll probably have damaged the mobs enough for the rest of your group to start mopping up.<br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, The Mad Mage of Povar<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
