	   <tr><td colspan=2>I simply can not understand why playing your mage is such a problem.  I will say here and now "I LOVE MY MAGE".  I love the fact that it is difficult to play the research is very challenging.  <br><br>Here is why...<br><br>1.  Grouping.  When gouping out doors or in a dungeon there is this spell called summon companion.  I can say that i have not had a single problem with my pet in a dungeon.  What i do is "Pet guard here".  walk to my next destination in the dungeon or where ever then summon companion.  Pet guard here again.  This method allows me to have complete control of my pet.  For those raids where the pet can be feared.  Your pet is just as sucepable as other charachters in the group but in the off chance that it does get feared.  There is the valiant companion spell at higher lvls and if all else fails invis your self and the pet will go.  I think the reason that we are not welcome in groups is because there are too many newbie mages that cant play their class.  I personally don't like to group much because there are some people out there in groups that play so many characters that they periodically forget the class they are playing is simply just don't know their role.<br><br>Soloing <br><br>this game is not as simple to play as an arcade game where you pay your money go in and kill stuff.  This game is about Strategy, research and most of all tactics.  the first step is to research a location to solo then weigh up the pros and cons of the site.  like how many hps does the mob have a mob with a lot of hit points means downtime.  That is why at higher levels mages are better off looking to hunt casters ie less hp = less mana to expire target.  The other thing is that casters nuke just like you so what you need here is strategy Eg i am fighting a warrior class ie flame bolt pull... pet... nuke.  fighting a caster class = low hps high damage output.  since you yourself cannot take the hits you let you pet tank right from the start.  This way he will take these hits because he is good for it.<br><br>Come on guys when i login at level 53 i feel 20 feet tall.  mostly because i know that if i learn one thing today that i can take with me into the next battle i will one day become the master of my class.<br><br>Lakarin G'kar bertoxx<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
