	   <tr><td colspan=2>#1 -- You just have to right click on it.  That will open the book and it will pop up similar to your spell book.  Actually you can read the books while meditating!  Gives you something do to!<br><br>#2 -- I have not figured that one out yet.  I have those 2 books, plus a 4 slot jewelry bag eating up 3 of my inventory/bank slots.  I have 8-pos backpacks in the remainder of my slots.  I continue to save items needed for research when I find them, so I am really running into a major inventory crunch.  I have been looking into tailoring so I can make 10 slot bags and maybe weight reducing bags as well.  Too expensive to buy right now when you must always save for that next set of spells!<br><br>#3 -- The practice research has been frustrating for me.  The second set of runes cannot be made -- apparently froglok eyes do not exist.  So I will be travelling to GFay from Qeynos to get wasp wings for the next set of runes.<br><br>Another suggestion -- do a lot of shopping!  Whenever you get to a new city, look around at the merchants to see what they have for sale.  Words, components, etc, can be purchased at merchants and may be the easiest place to get them.  I would rather try to find them on mobs myself, but I don't think that will always be possible.  For example, I found words of Trancendance at the Clerics guild in Rivervale.  Very happy with that find!  Those words are hard to find.<br><br>Also, try not to get frustrated.  I am working really hard on that one myself right now!  It will come, sometimes it just takes some time.<br><br>Hope this helps!<br>Good luck!<br><br>-Cidarenyae Halliwax<br>Mage of the 22nd season<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
