<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100423879165648></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100423879165648><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100423879165648>RE: Basic Research Questions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100423879165648#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=97944><span id=Scholar>harrije</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>26 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 27th 11:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Grimoire and Concordance are containers, just like boxes (or, more closely related, sewing kits). Just right-click to open.<br><br>How do I deal with carrying both books around? I just did. I actually kept one or both in the bank most of the time (and the grimoire is still there). My advice is to maximize your other inventory/bank slots by learning how to tailor handmade backpacks...those give you 10 slots and a minor weight reduction.<br><br>Froglok eyes are indeed in the game; you will need to travel to Upper Guk to find them. Actually, any frogloks should drop the eye, but Lower Guk is closest to the levels you'd be using them in the concordance.<br><br>Another option is just to save up a few platinum and pay the trainer for your skill points for a few levels. It's not too terribly expensive early on (but gets upwards of 50pp per point by later levels -- that's 50pp times 5 points times 5 levels between spells...well over 1kpp just to research your new spells).<br><br>Research components drop MUCH more frequently in dungeons than in general fighting areas. Level 24 items drop like candy in Solusek's Eye (A), for example. If you're not finding words, you're probably not fighting in the right places. Look for a dungeon with mobs around the level of the SPELL you need, and fight there a while.<br><br>That's easy enough now, but later on you'll find that you are fighting mobs more and more blue to you (even in groups) and less even or slightly above. You might have to start asking around (or auctioning) for the items from other characters. Make sure all your higher level friends know what you're looking for; many 49ish research drops are considered "junk" by the players who are fighting in those areas for experience, so they just get destroyed.<br><br>Good luck with your research; I find it amazing that while Magicians have possibly the hardest research path of all casters, they are more inclined to stick it out and practice the skills themselves. Only about 20% of necromancers I know actually research spells, the others just buy from other players. *shrug*<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

